sentences: Jane Marie Genevieve Wiedlin (born May 20, 1958) is an American musician, singer, songwriter and actress best known as the co-founder, rhythm guitarist and backing vocalist of the new wave band The Go-Go's.
She and the band were inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame on October 30, 2021.
Wiedlin was born May 20, 1958 in Oconomowoc, Waukesha County, Wisconsin.
